author: COMSOL
description:
Power lines are commonly used as a means of transmitting electrical power across large distances. In this tutorial, towers transmitting high voltage three-phase AC power are modeled, and the resulting magnetic field is computed. The towers have two shielding lines above the phase lines, which protect the tower from lightning strikes. 

The model uses the Magnetic Fields physics interface to compute the magnetic field.
label: power_line_magnetic_field.mph
